Description: CVE-2025-3198 - Fix objdump -i memory leak
 A memory leak flaw was found in the display_info() function in
 binutils/bucomm.c. The function allocates memory for arg.info via
 display_target_list() but never frees it before returning, leading
 to a memory leak. This patch adds the missing free(arg.info) call.
 .
 PR binutils/32716
Origin: upstream, https://sourceware.org/git/gitweb.cgi?p=binutils-gdb.git;a=commit;h=ba6ad3a18cb26b79e0e3b84c39f707535bbc344d
Bug: https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=32716
Author: Alan Modra <amodra@gmail.com>
Last-Update: 2025-02-19

--- a/binutils/bucomm.c
+++ b/binutils/bucomm.c
@@ -435,6 +435,7 @@ display_info (void)
   if (!arg.error)
     display_target_tables (&arg);

+  free (arg.info);
   return arg.error;
 }
