+---
+
+## Why CVE-2025-11081 Is a False Positive for **binutils 2.40** on Debian Bookworm
+
+---
+
+## 📌 CVE-2025-11081 – False Positive in binutils 2.40
+
+**Component:** `dump_dwarf_section` and `dump_sframe_section` in `objdump` (binutils)  
+**Issue:** SEGV when dumping `.sframe` in a PE file due to accessing `elf_section_data` without checking that the file is ELF format  
+**Impact:** Crash when running `objdump --sframe` or `objdump --dwarf` on non-ELF files (e.g. PE) on affected versions
+
+---
+
+## 🔍 Vulnerability Overview
+
+- **Component impacted:** `objdump` (`dump_dwarf_section`, `dump_sframe_section`)
+- **Nature of issue:** `elf_section_type()` macro is called without first verifying the BFD flavour is ELF, causing a NULL pointer dereference on PE files
+- **Severity:** Medium
+- **Attack vector:** Local file analysis – running `objdump` on a crafted non-ELF binary
+
+---
+
+## ✅ binutils 2.40 – Why This is a False Positive
+
+- **2.40 does not contain the vulnerable code** – the `elf_section_type()` calls in `dump_dwarf_section` and `dump_sframe_section` were introduced in a later binutils release (2.43+)
+- In 2.40, `dump_dwarf_section` (line 4382 of `objdump.c`) does **not** call `elf_section_type()` at all – there is no `SHT_GNU_SFRAME` check
+- In 2.40, `dump_section_sframe` (line 4878 of `objdump.c`) reads the section via `bfd_get_section_by_name()`, which is safe for any BFD format (ELF, PE, COFF, etc.)
+- A grep for `elf_section_type` in binutils 2.40's `objdump.c` returns **zero matches** – the vulnerable code path simply does not exist
+- The upstream fix (commit `f87a66db645c`) adds `bfd_get_flavour(abfd) == bfd_target_elf_flavour` guards before `elf_section_type()` calls that **do not exist in 2.40**
+- Debian Security Tracker may mark it as "vulnerable" due to broad version tagging, not code presence
+
+---
+
+## ⚠️ Why You Don't Need to Fix It
+
+- **No vulnerable code present in 2.40** – `elf_section_type()` is never called in `dump_dwarf_section` or `dump_sframe_section`
+- **No security impact** on Debian bookworm systems
+- **False positive from scanners** due to generic CVE matching on `binutils`
+- The upstream patch is **not applicable** to 2.40 because the code it modifies was introduced after 2.40
+
+---
+
+## 🔗 References
+
+- [**NVD Entry – CVE-2025-11081**](https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-11081)
+- [**Debian binutils 2.40 (bookworm)**](https://packages.debian.org/bookworm/binutils)
+- [**Upstream fix commit – f87a66db645c**](https://sourceware.org/git/?p=binutils-gdb.git;a=commit;h=f87a66db645caf8cc0e6fc87b0c28c78a38af59b)
+- [**Upstream bug – PR 33406**](https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=33406)
