 function in bfd/elflink.c. When processing ELF files with empty global symbol
 names (name[0] == '\0'), the linker does not validate for this condition,
 leading to an out-of-bounds read. This patch adds validation to reject ELF
 files with corrupt (empty) symbol names. The check is placed after the
 add_symbol_hook processing, giving the backend hook a chance to handle or
 remove symbols with empty names before the validation occurs.
Origin: upstream, commit:72efdf166aa0ed72ecc69fc2349af6591a7a19c0
Bug: https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=33452
