Description: CVE-2024-53589 - Fix tekhex object file output buffer overflow
 GNU objdump is vulnerable to a buffer overflow in the BFD library's handling
 of tekhex format files. The vulnerability occurs in the first_phase function
 within tekhex.c, where improper handling of the bfd_abs_section pointer leads
 to a global buffer overflow. This patch adds const-section guards to prevent
 writing to special constant sections (bfd_abs_section, bfd_und_section, etc.)
 and moves the addr variable to function scope to avoid dangling references.
Origin: upstream, commit:e0323071916878e0634a6e24d8250e4faff67e88
